      <description>&lt;p&gt;A card game by &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.logicmazes.com/games/eleusis/&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Robert Abbott&lt;span style=&#34;white-space: nowrap;&#34;&gt;&amp;thinsp;↗&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Each round one player is God (dealer) and other players are scientists.&#xA;God makes up a rule and scientists are trying to get rid of their cards by playing them accodring to the rule.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The following picture shows one possible layout of cards at the end of one round.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;drawing.svg&#34; alt=&#34;A sample card layout for a round in Eleusis&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
